pic.jpg height=200 width=152></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Cargo Clockwork - how?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I can't help you with Cargo, but I can tell you you might want to leave the leeches alone. They hit very hard and fast for their level (very difficult to channel through), guards won't help you if things go badly, and they have *zilch* loot.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure this is viable at 31, but at 32, I started killing drachnids in FV. There is too much traffic in the area to kite them (you will either get mobbed by other drachs or KS'd by pilgrims and drixies). Root-and-nuke worked fine if you picked your fights carefully and weren't afraid to gate out if things started to go south. I bound by the bank - that way if I had poison and a drach dot on me, I could holler for a heal and cure; the area is nearly always populated with some type of healer.<br>
<br>
I died on a regular basis hunting drachnids, but the fast xp more than made up for it. I spent 2-3 months each on levels 30 and 31 in the old world, and averaged a week per level in Kunark right up to 51.</font><P><b>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</b><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE>